LAGOS – Twenty-two students of the Caleb University, Imota, Lagos State, have emerged beneficiaries of Dr Akintoye Akindele Scholarship scheme for 100 students. The Chairman of the Screening Committee, Professor Oluwole Alagbe, Dean, COLENSMA, explained, “The 22 excellent students emerged after a rigorous process of selection by a Special Panel set up by the University Management. Students who recorded the highest Cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA) across the departments, were shortlisted, screened and subsequently awarded the Scholarship,” Alagbe added. Recall that In March 2022, the oil magnate, philanthropist and entrepreneur, Dr Akintoye Akindele, who was the 11th convocation lecturer announced a scholarship scheme for 1% (22 students) of the newly admitted students. Besides, at the event, Dr Akindele reaffirmed his plans to establish a Research Centre for African History and Archaeology, as well as a Unicorn Innovation and Incubation Centre at the Imota Campus of Caleb University. While addressing 100 Level Students during the ‘Agogo’ Programme, themed: ‘The Sound of Transformation’, the 22 recipients were formally presented to the University Community. The Vice-Chancellor, Prof. Nosa Owens Ibie congratulated the recipients and urged them to sustain the tempo, saying the Scholarship runs through the final year, provided they maintain the minimum benchmark of 4.50 CGPA. Among the recipients were Idowu Priscilla Oluwatosin, Tamunokonbua Joy Soala and Nwagbo Joy Chioma all with a perfect score of 5.00 CGPA, among others. POLL The Dr Akintoye Akindele Scholarship is an inclusive education award that recognizes indigent 100-level students who have kick-started their academic endeavours on an excellent note. The prize aims to progress learning by advancing the vision of Caleb University Founding Fathers; to be an innovative leader in producing impactful human resources, and sustaining excellence in learning, service and godly character.